[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T18:29:17+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A MacBook Pro box being held between two hands so that the top label is facing the camera.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qIAEKIuk6lJKuQ9jGIBf01FSauA=/182x0:2074x1261/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73638382/Screenshot_2024_10_07_at_4.37.09_PM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Is this the M4 MacBook Pro?</em> | Screenshot: YouTube</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"bATaT8\">At least two Russian creators have posted videos in which they unbox what appears to be the next base model 14-inch MacBook Pro with an M4 chip. Apple, which hasn\u2019t announced the laptops yet, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/6/24263414/apple-m4-macs-november-rumor-small-mac-mini-macbook-pro-imac-ipad-mini\">is rumored to have a launch planned</a> for November.</p>\n<p id=\"kjBjhI\">Over the weekend, <em>Bloomberg</em>\u2019s Mark Gurman <a href=\"https://www.threads.net/@markgurman/post/DAzEwnMTEwS?xmt=AQGzqEKUFutH3PXaY07wOuOIA9Y2eABNXXGlmV8sdisjqw\">pointe", "id": 1283759, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264707/apple-m4-macbook-pro-russia-leak-video", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple\u2019s next MacBook Pros might have leaked in Russia", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T18:15:34+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"light blue truck parked in front of body of water\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0wrqi2y9WIVFG9jdWY2WWOh7SOk=/0x0:1828x1219/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73638352/2025_chevrolet_silverado_ev_lt_001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The new midrange LT model gets the light-up Chevy logo.</em> | Image: Chevy</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"XNpHF9\">Chevy is <a href=\"https://pressroom.chevrolet.com/gmbx/us/en/chevrolet/pressroom/news.detail.html/Pages/news/us/en/2024/oct/1007-silveradoev.html\">lowering the Silverado EV\u2019s starting price for 2025</a> by adding a new standard range Work Truck (WT) version that starts at $57,095, which includes destination charges but not other fees, and Chevy says the dealer \u201csets final price.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"QYuvf2\">Chevy also added several additional versions of the electric truck with varying ranges compared to the outgoing 2024 model with only one version, the RST trim, priced at nearly $100,", "id": 1283760, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264622/chevy-silverado-ev-2025-wt-lt-rst", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Chevy\u2019s cheapest Silverado EV now starts at $57,095", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T16:50:32+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of Sundar Pichai and Tim Sweeney with the Google logo, Google Play logo, and the Epic Games logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Go7NLkEsItmkIuu7RAJrwri1EaA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72834514/236883_Epic_Vs_Google_D_CVirginia.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo illustration by Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos by Philip Pacheco, Bloomberg, Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>The jury and judge sided with Epic, and it may change Android apps forever.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23945184/epic-v-google-fortnite-play-store-antitrust-trial-updates\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1283356, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23945184/epic-v-google-fortnite-play-store-antitrust-trial-updates", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Epic v. Google: everything we learned in Fortnite court", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T16:47:33+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"iPhone showing Sleep Schedules within the Health app\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/AxGdboxtSYkRPcvOcK2l_L2Fp-w=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/71221866/IMG_0376.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Sleep schedules offer a few ways to automate your sleep routine.</em> | Photo by Victoria Song / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"F1qJjL\">With iOS 14, Apple introduced the ability to set your sleep schedules in the Health app. The feature itself isn\u2019t too complicated. You figure out how many hours you ideally want to get every night, then set a scheduled bedtime and wake time that suits that goal. </p>\n<p id=\"ditQdx\">Of course, you could always just set up a one-time or repeating alarm within the Clock app. The main reason why you\u2019d opt for a sleep schedule instead is that it allows you to set a specific goal and more easily automate a sleep routine. For example, you can automatically launch the Sleep Foc", "id": 1283357, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23296761/sleep-schedules-ios-health-app-how-to", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to set up sleep schedules in iOS", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T16:42:49+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A satellite image of a large hurricane swirling over the Gulf of Mexico.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/fsAtHJXK1M6lmzv2HoFnIT1Oqnw=/0x334:2000x1667/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73638179/GZTKNDfaQAA5M0B__1_.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Hurricane Milton swirls over the Gulf of Mexico.</em> | Image: NOAA</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"DTvFjE\">Hurricane Milton strengthened into a Category 5 storm today, becoming one of the most rapidly intensifying storms ever in the history of the Atlantic hurricane season. </p>\n<p id=\"SN5d8f\">It\u2019s likely <a href=\"https://www.cnn.com/weather/live-news/hurricane-milton-florida-10-07-2024/index.html\">within the top three fastest storms</a> on record when it comes to rapid intensification, used to describe tropical cyclones with sustained wind speeds that increase by at least 30 knots (roughly 35 miles per hour) in a 24-hour period. Milton has seen an 80-knot increase in wind speed ", "id": 1283358, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264419/hurricane-milton-category-5-storm-rapid-intensification-climate-change", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Another major hurricane is approaching Florida, one of the most rapidly intensifying on record ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T15:54:09+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot showing a man wearing a Vision Pro headset.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kdEMHFG9zQ191MfD1OAigBwIT3U=/87x0:1049x641/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73638044/Screenshot_2024_10_07_at_1.58.18_PM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Director Edward Berger wears a Vision Pro headset in the trailer for </em>Submerged. | Screenshot: YouTube</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"XUwYT0\">Apple just released the trailer for <em>Submerged</em>, the first scripted immersive video for the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24054862/apple-vision-pro-review-vr-ar-headset-features-price\">Vision Pro</a>. The short, written and directed by Edward Berger, is set inside a WWII submarine as its crew deals with \u201ca harrowing torpedo attack.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"tqs10T\">The trailer for <em>Submerged</em> consists of behind-the-scenes shots and fisheye-looking clips from the short, along with a voiceover from Berger, who claims that the immersive f", "id": 1282908, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264457/apple-submerged-trailer-vision-pro-immersive-video", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Watch this one-minute preview of Apple\u2019s first scripted Vision Pro short", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T15:49:42+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Amazon\u2019s logo on a black, orange, and tan background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/AY8zgGy5TwlkkPcDnIgvVOVGt0c=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73638038/acastro_STK103__01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"n9aMhY\">A federal judge gave the Federal Trade Commission the green light to pursue antitrust claims against Amazon, <a href=\"https://www.courtlistener.com/docket/67828404/289/federal-trade-commission-v-amazoncom-inc/\">a newly unsealed order reveals</a>, though some claims under state laws won\u2019t move forward.</p>\n<p id=\"wiBBnU\">Amazon filed a motion to dismiss <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/26/23809817/amazon-ftc-antitrust-lawsuit-monopoly\">the 2023 lawsuit</a>, which alleges the company illegally maintains a monopoly by punishing sellers who discount products outside of Amazon and \u201ceffectively requires\u201d them t", "id": 1282909, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264605/ftc-amazon-antitrust-motion-to-dismiss", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Judge greenlights FTC\u2019s antitrust suit against Amazon", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T14:48:18+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of the Epic Games logo and Google logo inside of a Google Play logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/pLoqMWQwaxPit5DCZYxv-UtTEdI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73637898/236883_Epic_Vs_Google_B_CVirginia.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"B43bj3\">Google\u2019s Android app store <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23994174/epic-google-trial-jury-verdict-monopoly-google-play\">is an illegal monopoly</a> \u2014 and now it will have to change. </p>\n<p id=\"XxAtcK\">Today, Judge James Donato issued his final ruling <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23945184/epic-v-google-fortnite-play-store-antitrust-trial-updates\">in <em>Epic v. Google</em></a>, ordering Google to effectively open up the Google Play app store to competition for three whole years. Google will have to distribute rival third-party app stores<em> within </em>Google Play, and it must", "id": 1282563, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/policy/2024/10/7/24243316/epic-google-permanent-injunction-ruling-third-party-stores", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google must crack open Android for third-party stores, rules Epic judge", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T13:03:14+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from Alien Isolation featuring a close up shot of the alien xenomorph.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xWqeg59-rxmM3fyPZ4WTQlLBzTs=/306x0:3695x2259/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73637676/alienisolation5.0.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Creative Assembly</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"zvrbvF\">To celebrate the tenth anniversary of the release of <em>Alien: Isolation</em>, the developers at Creative Assembly <a href=\"https://x.com/AlienIsolation/status/1843305291322200488\">has announced they\u2019re working on a sequel</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"zvKyuv\">\u201cWe have heard your distress calls loud and clear,\u201d wrote Al Hope, creative director at Creative Assembly. \u201cI\u2019m delighted to confirm, on behalf of the team, that a sequel to <em>Alien: Isolation</em> is in early development.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"y9AiIV\"><em>Alien: Isolation</em> released in 2014 <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2014/10/3/6897307/alien-isolation-review\">to rave re", "id": 1281600, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264348/alien-isolation-sequel-creative-assembly-sega", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "It\u2019s a spooky season miracle, Alien: Isolation is getting a sequel", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T12:44:02+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Inside The 2019 Consumer Electronics Show\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ZujLP3Dbccs_GtvhBxs9Dljwf-s=/0x0:4000x2667/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73637629/1078648890.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"DDYzch\">Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang will deliver a keynote at CES 2025 in January. The keynote <a href=\"https://www.ces.tech/press-releases/nvidia-ceo-jensen-huang-to-deliver-ces-2025-keynote/\">will take place</a> on January 6th at 6:30PM PT / 9:30PM ET, just a day before the Consumer Electronics Show opens its doors in Las Vegas. It comes amid rumors of next-gen Nvidia GPUs appearing early next year.</p>\n<p id=\"zv3r8g\">A source familiar with Nvidia\u2019s plans <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/26/24255234/nvidia-rtx-5090-5080-specs-leak#:~:text=I%20understand%20from%20one%20source%20familiar%20with%20Nvidia%E2%80%99s%20plans\">told <em>The Verge</em> last month</a> that we might hear", "id": 1281601, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264418/nvidia-ces-2025-keynote-rtx-5090-rumors", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nvidia to hold CES 2025 keynote as RTX 5090 rumors swirl", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T12:33:37+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Threads logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kV46AGmeT8eiuSmMyVhJrzDPKJc=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73637613/STK156_Instagram_threads_1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"4KS0H0\">If you\u2019ve noticed more engagement bait appearing across your Threads feed, you\u2019re not alone. Meta is aware of the issue and looking at how to address it, according to Instagram boss Adam Mosseri. \u201cWe\u2019ve seen an increase in engagement-bait on Threads and we\u2019re working to get it under control,\u201d <a href=\"https://www.threads.net/@mosseri/post/DA01Sd8vtm6?xmt=AQGzUEHIfkz9GI69LUpjuFbpQGH2xxfXVoYiy77fnco-Rg\">Mosseri said on Threads</a> in response to comments flagging the issue. </p>\n<p id=\"lFc2OC\">Engagement bait on Threads typically covers posts with banal questions or invites for open-ended discussions to encourage other users to interact. Because Threads, lik", "id": 1281602, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264382/threads-engagement-bait-problem-mosseri-meta", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Threads knows it has an engagement bait problem", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T12:30:40+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of a Tesla Cybertruck.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2F0Qo1d3kZGTCzgMF9VyV4cRKtY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73637607/236937_Cybertruck_CVirginia.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>The Verge / Photo by Bloomberg, Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"LPlrAu\">Geico says it still offers insurance for Tesla\u2019s Cybertruck after some customers reported being dropped by their insurance company for the expensive and unconventional electric truck.</p>\n<p id=\"nZhNS1\"><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/CyberStuck/comments/1fx4oyn/apparently_geico_car_insurance_in_no_longer/\">Several owners have reported</a> difficulties in procuring coverage for their Cybertrucks, fueling speculation that the insurance industry was refusing to write policies for the truck. The speculation reached a fever pitch this weekend when <a href=\"https://www.torquenews.com/11826/geico-terminating-insurance-coverage-tes", "id": 1281603, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264330/geico-insurance-coverage-cybertruck-cancelled-dropped-policy", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Geico insists it \u2018has coverage\u2019 for the Cybertruck after owners complain of dropped policies", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T12:02:34+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of a computer screen with a blue exclamation point on it and an error box.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/b1S9F0ULkrpY9o9vrRGco6yZntI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73637539/akrales_220309_4977_0232.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"a9ltK8\">A data breach has exposed the names, addresses, social security numbers, and birthdates of more than 237,700 Comcast customers. The breach stems from a security incident at Financial Business and Consumer Solutions (FBCS), a debt collection agency Comcast previously used, according to a <a href=\"https://www.maine.gov/agviewer/content/ag/985235c7-cb95-4be2-8792-a1252b4f8318/aff9fd91-81e8-4d95-a84e-c56f1d48f088.html?7194ef805fa2d04b0f7e8c9521f97343\">filing with the state of Maine</a> on Friday, as reported <a href=\"https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/comcast-and-truist-bank-cu", "id": 1281604, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264283/comcast-fcbs-data-breach-ssn-names", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Data breach leaks SSNs of over 230,000 Comcast customers", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T11:33:37+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Jesse Lyu stares at camera\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Ui-m-kjLUtlnIwlLIU_Xjid--mI=/1x0:2760x1839/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73637412/DCD_Jesse_Lyu.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo illustration by The Verge / Photo: Rabbit</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Rabbit\u2019s large action model is here, sort of \u2014 but everyone else is coming fast.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24260181/rabbit-r1-large-action-model-lam-playground-generative-ai-jesse-lyu-interview-users\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1280967, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24260181/rabbit-r1-large-action-model-lam-playground-generative-ai-jesse-lyu-interview-users", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Rabbit CEO Jesse Lyu isn\u2019t thinking too far ahead", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T11:19:03+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of a hand holding an Apple Pencil Pro.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0UjVt5mExLbBYHRjaq_Xza0i0YU=/0x0:6000x4000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73637381/DSC08748.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Apple Pencil Pro is a much easier recommendation at $99.</em> | Photo: David Pierce / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"fwmBOu\">Spending another $129 to get the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/7/24146454/apple-pencil-pro-ipad-stylus-price-availability-features\"><strong>Apple Pencil Pro</strong></a> after upgrading to the latest iPad Pro and iPad Air devices is a hard pill to swallow. That pill is a little bit smaller now, thankfully.  It\u2019s currently discounted to $99 ($30 off) at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0D3J71RM7?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a>, <a href=\"https://goto.walmart.com/c/482924/2090038/9383?subId1=verge100724&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2F", "id": 1280968, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264200/apple-pencil-pro-pixel-watch-3-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple Pencil Pro drops under $100 for the first time", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T10:47:30+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A picture of the Sansui OLED from the front.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/It8woX8ki30r9AuoWzFunGG-UAk=/56x0:1744x1125/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73637321/Sansui_OLED.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>That\u2019s a cheap OLED.</em> | Image: Sansui</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ou9Xy4\">Last week, Sansui debuted a new 4K 120Hz 55-inch OLED TV (S55VOUG) that\u2019s <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.prweb.com%2Freleases%2Fsansui-launches-flagship-55-inch-oled-tv-with-120hz-refresh-rate-starting-at-just-799-302265225.html&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F10%2F7%2F24264214%2Fsansui-55-inch-4k-oled-tv-budget-price-ai-karaoke-mode-youtube\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">available now for between</a> $799 and $899 \u201cdepending on retailer promotions.\u201d </p>\n<p id=\"pra3fa\">The new OLED\u2019s list price is the higher of those", "id": 1280969, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264214/sansui-55-inch-4k-oled-tv-budget-price-ai-karaoke-mode-youtube", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sansui\u2019s new 55-inch 4K OLED is just $799 ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T10:39:02+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"ChargeScape logo, two stacked thunderbolts with the text to the right\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/F3iRxFyjWoKTO8ufab7KxSnw-I0=/0x175:3300x2375/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73637303/ChargeScap_Horiz_Blue.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: ChargeScape</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Iw8jcQ\">Nissan is <a href=\"https://usa.nissannews.com/en-US/releases/chargescape-welcomes-nissan-to-its-alliance-of-automakers-helping-ev-drivers-save-money-on-at-home-charging\">coming aboard vehicle-to-grid (V2G) EV integration company</a> ChargeScape as an equal investor, alongside founding automakers BMW, Ford, and Honda. </p>\n<p id=\"t94xYj\">Once the investment transaction is complete, Nissan said it plans to roll out ChargeScape\u2019s services to its electric vehicle customers in the US and Canada.</p>\n<p id=\"Q6L07g\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/12/23870267/ford-honda-bmw-ev-v2g-company-chargescape\">Formed last year</a> (<a ", "id": 1280970, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264241/nissan-chargescape-investment-ev-home-v2g", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nissan buys into Ford, BMW, and Honda\u2019s home EV charging business", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T10:37:51+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A person holding a pair of Sony WH-1000XM4 headphones.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/FlDBvEJXmtFg6bTxf2_wRp15Y-Y=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73637301/IMG_0640_1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Chris Welch / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"c003oM\">Amazon\u2019s<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/amazon-prime-day-deals-tech\"> Prime Big Deal Days</a> sales event begins tomorrow, but the best tech deal around may have already landed early. The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/21356313/sony-1000xm4-noise-canceling-headphones-review-price-specs-features\"><strong>Sony WH-1000XM4</strong></a> noise-canceling headphones have dropped to a new all-time low of $129.99 ($220 off) at <a href=\"https://goto.target.com/c/482924/81938/2092?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.target.com%2Fp%2Fsony-wh-1000xm4-noise-canceling-overhead-bluetooth-wireless-headphones-silver%2F-%2FA-79757338%3Fpreselect%3D79757327&amp;sharedid=the", "id": 1280971, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24264257/sony-wh1000xm4-noise-canceling-headphones-amazon-prime-deal-days-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The last-gen Sony WH-1000XM4 headphones are now a staggering $220 off", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T10:30:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of the menu from Metaphor: ReFantazio.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/s0uWg4l10814W-BnmoRFgrSAXdQ=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73637273/ss_6956a6d6ff1745101aa0cd4a8445ff2d19853bfa.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Atlus</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"wu3y70\"><em>Persona</em> is one of the rare video game series where people actually talk about the menus. They\u2019re functional, sure, but they\u2019re also so incredibly stylish that you almost don\u2019t mind constantly pausing to equip gear or heal your party. So when I had the chance to talk to longtime<em> Persona</em> director Katsura Hashino about his new game, <em>Metaphor: ReFantazio</em>, which continues this tradition of beautiful menus, I had to ask how they do it.</p>\n<p id=\"NTNXKZ\">The answer, as Hashino explains it, is simply a lot of work:</p>\n<blockquote><p id=\"HzuN42\">In general, the way most game developers make UI is very simple. T", "id": 1280972, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24262357/persona-metaphor-menu-design", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Persona director says making beautiful menus is \u2018actually really annoying\u2019", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T10:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/YeMOSgVlzlChdBYryHy-5YdbR-Q=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73637186/edit_2.00_00_00_09.Still001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Vjeran Pavic / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"4LYxvu\">The iPhone 16 Pro\u2019s camera upgrades may be the true highlights of this year\u2019s phone. So, for the past three weeks, <em>The Verge</em> supervising producer Vjeran Pavic has been testing out everything the camera has to offer.</p>\n<p id=\"hWir7l\">Apple\u2019s new Camera Control button may be the headline feature, but the iPhone 16 is also equipped with a suite of new photo adjustment tools that let you dial in individual aspects of how an image looks. Apple also beefed up the phone\u2019s recording capabilities, which can capture 120fps 4K in slow motion while shooting in ProRes in Apple Log.  </p>\n<div id=\"mcR028\"><div data-anthem-component=\"imageslider:12446247\"></div></div>\n<p id=\"nw1EBn", "id": 1280415, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24261280/iphone-16-pro-camera-guide-features-camera-control-button", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "A professional\u2019s guide to the iPhone 16 Pro camera", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T10:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot from the video game Metaphor: ReFantazio.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/MtN0cdJ0JHmjnuF5GzNJySZ-k7g=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73637192/ss_527790d51f418e98fb04819221a348103c85a69b.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Metaphor: ReFantazio.</em> | Image: Atlus</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"pm9qM4\"><em>Persona 5</em> helped the roleplaying franchise <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2017/3/29/15098458/persona-5-review-ps4-ps3\">break out with mainstream audiences</a>, and it\u2019s also a game that was in the works for a long time. Early work began in 2008, just after <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/12/5/20994037/playstation-jrpg-persona-series-atlus-final-fantasy-4-vii-xenogears-kingdom-hearts-25-anniversary\"><em>Persona 4</em></a> came out, with full development kicking off three years later. So, just ahead of the game\u2019s launch in 2016, director Katsura Hashino \u2014 steward of the franchis", "id": 1280414, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24262346/metaphor-refantazio-katsura-hashino-interview-persona", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Why Persona\u2019s longtime director made an epic fantasy RPG", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T08:14:40+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"iPhone with homepage icons against an illustrated background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/fv8GU3sl-xQ4qMkVHKfJB0Y8ucc=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73636980/HT015_S_Haddad_ios_iphone_14_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Samar Haddad / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"8fqGez\">For several years now, it\u2019s been possible to personalize your iPhone screen by creating your own icons, mostly by using Apple\u2019s built-in Shortcuts app (<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22529978/apple-iphone-ios-apps-icon-change\">and we have instructions for doing just that</a>). But if you want to do a little customization in a short amount of time, a new feature in iOS 18 lets you tweak the color of your app icons in a matter of moments. Here\u2019s how.</p>\n<p id=\"Gaz5bP\">On your iPhone homescreen:</p>\n<ul>\n<li id=\"WNFbxV\">Long-press somewhere on the background so that the icons start to do their little jiggle", "id": 1279811, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24260660/ios-18-iphone-icons-color-how-to", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to tint your app icons in iOS 18", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-07T08:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot from the video game Phoenix Springs.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NcrEfEnHo5DNudhiVXAgNySPo9Y=/125x0:1475x900/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73636933/Iris_1.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Calligram Studio</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p class=\"p--has-dropcap\" id=\"MtdHP5\">In <em>Phoenix Springs</em>, it\u2019s not so much the ravishing hand-drawn visuals that first grab the attention, but the voice of narrator and protagonist Iris. Befitting her name, she behaves like a roving eye, investigating and describing her surroundings with a clinical, almost robotic detachment. Yet Iris is no blank slate: you quickly come to learn that she is a snob with little regard for the homeless. She even appears to have short shrift for the player, delivering a withering putdown when you make a connection she deems just a little <em>too</em> obvious.</p>\n<p id=\"CYBUWj\">Iris, a tech journalist by trade, is the perfect protagoni", "id": 1279812, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/7/24262101/phoenix-springs-review-point-and-click-adventure", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Phoenix Springs reimagines the point-and-click adventure as weird noir", "vote": 0}]